= Rutherford B. Hayes

Rutherford B. Hayes of Ohio is a war hero whose combat record speaks for itself—wounded five times, promoted to brevet major general for valor. Unlike many Republican politicians, Hayes carries the credibility of genuine sacrifice. His reputation for integrity and honesty is uncommon in an era of machine politics and corruption scandals.

Hayes represents the moderate Republican who believes in Reconstruction without radicalism, and in honest government without self-dealing. As Chairman of the Joint Committee on the Library of Congress, he controls significant cultural patronage. His standing with the Army officer corps remains strong from his wartime service.

