@hayes_border_state_outreach
title: Appeal to Border State Unionists
subtitle: Hayes reaches out to former Whigs and conditional Unionists in Kentucky, Missouri, and Maryland.
choose-if: advisor_action_timer = 0
unavailable-subtitle: [? if advisor_action_timer > 0 : [+ advisor_action_timer +] months before next advisor action. ?]
on-arrival: advisor_action_timer = 6; last_advisor_action = 1; KY_middle_class_rep += 4; KY_rural_rep += 3; MO_middle_class_rep += 3; MO_rural_rep += 2; MD_middle_class_rep += 3; WV_rural_rep += 2;

Hayes, as a border state Republican himself, understands the hesitation of former Whigs and conditional Unionists. His war record and moderate approach appeal to those who want Union restored without social revolution. He travels the border states, speaking to merchants, lawyers, and farmers who fear both radical change and Democratic restoration. Support grows among those who see Hayes as a safe Republican choice.

@hayes_library_committee
title: Use Library Committee Influence
subtitle: Hayes directs Library of Congress patronage and resources toward Republican cultural institutions.
choose-if: advisor_action_timer = 0
unavailable-subtitle: [? if advisor_action_timer > 0 : [+ advisor_action_timer +] months before next advisor action. ?]
on-arrival: advisor_action_timer = 6; last_advisor_action = 1;
go-to: media

As Chairman of the Joint Committee on the Library of Congress, Hayes controls significant cultural patronage—library acquisitions, manuscript collections, and appointments. He directs funds toward Republican newspapers' archives, supports loyal historians and scholars, and ensures that the narrative of the war and Reconstruction is told favorably. The Library becomes a tool of Republican cultural influence. Conservatives grumble about intellectual waste; liberals appreciate the support for learning.

@hayes_army_loyalty
title: Strengthen Army Officer Loyalty
subtitle: Hayes leverages his standing with Union officers to improve Army loyalty to Republican government.
choose-if: advisor_action_timer = 0
unavailable-subtitle: [? if advisor_action_timer > 0 : [+ advisor_action_timer +] months before next advisor action. ?]
on-arrival: advisor_action_timer = 6; last_advisor_action = 1; army_loyalty += 0.1;

Hayes, still trusted by the officer corps from his wartime service, works quietly with key generals and colonels to ensure that the Army remains loyal to the Republican government and committed to Reconstruction. His credibility with military men—built on five combat wounds and genuine battlefield valor—opens doors that other Republican politicians cannot access. Officer loyalty strengthens.